Happy Pride Month! Watch how the King Arthur Baking community is kicking off celebrations. ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜

"We celebrate Pride because we are committed to a more diverse and inclusive future — and we want to show up for each other." - Karen Colberg, King Arthur Baking co-CEO

King Arthur Baking Company is making a donation to @TheTrevorProject, which provides crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer & questioning (LGBTQ) young people under 25. We encourage you to learn more and donate at bakewith.us/TrevorProject

node.title: Celebrate Pride With Us - King Arthur Baking Company - Pride 2021

node.text:
Have you heard? Theatre on the Hill is at King Arthur Baking Company here in Norwich, VT! Every weekend through September 12, we’re hosting live outdoor theatre from @jagproductionsvt, here on the hill next to our Cafe, Bakery, Store and Baking School in Norwich, VT! 

We’re proud to partner with JAG Productions from White River Junction, whose mission as a theatre company is to bring compassion, empathy, love, and community through the lens of the African American experience.

JAG will be presenting workshops, concerts, burlesques, and staged readings, each of which illuminates Black life and aesthetics. King Arthur's courtyard opens at 6:30 p.m. ET every Friday, Saturday, and Sunday during the series, where you can enjoy local food and beverages before the show starts at 8 p.m. on the hill. 

Tickets are on sale now! Adult themes and language — parental guidance suggested. For more info and tickets, visit the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking

We hope to see you on the hill!

node.text: Sweet, but not sugary, these tender scones are packed with ripe, summer blueberries and a hefty dose of bright lemon zest. node.text: What’s a sundae without hot fudge? Ice cream ... it’s just ice cream. We can do better than that! Complete your sundae with a batch of gloriously smooth, rich, and shiny fudge sauce. Add a splash of your favorite liqueur at the end for an extra-special treat. Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your ice cream dressed in its sundae best with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: Wetter can be better when it comes to bread dough. Lending an open crumb structure, a good oven spring, and that satisfying “holey” look, high-hydration doughs are all the rage. But is wet dough always the answer to better bread? Find out in @breadwright’s latest article at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your next loaf with #KingArthurBaking

node.text: How do you know your Perfectly Pillow Cinnamon rolls are ready to bake? Give them the Poke Test! If your finger indent stays, they're ready to pop in the oven. See it in action with our #recipeoftheyear at bakewith.us/ROTY2021

node.text: Taking a trip down memory lane, @chefsusaninvt is making the cherry pie her mother used to make for her and her 5 siblings. Not too sweet, not too tart. Just perfectly buttery, beautiful, and nostalgic. Follow along by tapping the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your pie with #KingArthurBaking. Don’t forget to tag Susan @chefsusaninvt so she can see it too!

node.text: Putting a spicy twist on her grandmother’s classic Coca-Cola cake, Chef @Carlaphall created her recipe for Root Beer Cake with Chocolate Root Beer Ganache. With an extra kick from fresh ginger, smoked cinnamon, and star anise, this fragrant, fudgy Bundt is a must! Find the recipe at the link in our profile >> @kingarthurbaking, and share your cake with #KingArthurBaking
